CIT Group Inc., the once-bankrupt
business lender run by  John Thain , has reinstated a dividend.  The quarterly dividend of 10 cents a share is payable on
Nov. 29 to shareholders of record as of Nov. 15, the New York-based company said today in a statement distributed by Business
Wire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
